#: ./Spencer.dialog:37
msgid "Greetings fellow Red Guard member."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:45
#: ./Spencer.dialog:50
#: ./Spencer.dialog:277
msgid "Opening access to MS Office"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:45
msgid "A kingdom for a cluster!"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:49
#: ./Spencer.dialog:299
msgid "Propagating a faulty firmware"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:54
#: ./Spencer.dialog:122
msgid "Deliverance"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:63
msgid "Hi! I'm new here."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:65
msgid ""
"I'm Spencer. I'm the leader of the Red Guard. Is there anything I can help you"
" with?"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:70
msgid "I want to join the Red Guard."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:72
msgid "Hmm... Really? Well, you cannot join just like that, you know..."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:73
msgid "You must prove that you would make a good new member."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:78
msgid "I really want to become a member."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:80
msgid ""
"This is not so easy. First you must establish a reputation around here. Ask ar"
"ound, talk to people and build your reputation."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:81
msgid ""
"Once you're a known character around here, we might let you join the ranks of "
"the Guard."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:86
msgid "How about some circuits instead?"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:88
msgid "For 15 million circuits, no less, hehe."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:94
msgid "But I don't have that many circuits!"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:96
msgid "That much I can tell."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:97
msgid "Look, I'm just fooling around. We don't let just anyone join the Red Guard."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:98
msgid ""
"If you seriously want to join, you have to prove yourself first. You might wan"
"t to ask around town for things you can do."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:104
msgid "Francis wanted me to give you this."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:108
msgid "Ah, excellent, the list I asked for."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:109
msgid "It figures he would ask someone to deliver it for him."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:110
msgid "Why's that?"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:111
msgid ""
"We had a little disagreement, Francis and I. He refused to accept our rule and"
" do the task we gave him."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:112
msgid "I had to persuade him myself."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:113
msgid "Did you beat him up?"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:114
msgid ""
"No, nothing so violent. Let's just say I know more about Francis than he would"
" like to remember."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:115
msgid "Anyway, we haven't exactly been close friends since."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:116
msgid "Why didn't he want to do this task you gave him? What was it?"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:117
msgid ""
"I wanted him to go through the people in cryogenic freezing in the facility, a"
"nd make a list of disposable ones and people unlikely to survive. This cube co"
"ntains that list."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:118
msgid ""
"Disposable people? Unlikely to survive? Can't they just stay in cryogenics ind"
"efinitely?"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:119
msgid ""
"No. They take up a lot of space, and keeping them alive takes a lot of power, "
"which is running out. Most of the people there are sick or dying anyway, which"
" is why they're frozen in the first place. We can't afford to waste any resour"
"ces."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:120
msgid ""
"We even had to confiscate the town cook's macrowave oven battery, which means "
"we can't eat warm food anymore. We needed it to keep the town's defenses up."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:122
msgid ""
"I gave Spencer the data cube. Apparently it was a list of people in freezing i"
"n the cryogenic facility. Spencer wants to dispose of some of them because kee"
"ping them alive uses up the town's power..."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:126
msgid "... What?"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:127
msgid "Oh, erm... Hehe, I think I forgot it somewhere."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:128
msgid "Then you had better go and look for it. Don't waste my time, Linarian."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:134
msgid "Maybe I could help somehow?"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:136
msgid ""
"That would be most kind of you, but I doubt that you will be able to clear out"
" the warehouse for us."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:137
msgid ""
"But since you are said to be powerful and a former hero, I'll once more put tr"
"ust into a stranger."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:138
msgid ""
"I've unlocked the access-way to the warehouse. It's to the north of this town,"
" somewhat hidden in the woods northeast."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:139
msgid ""
"The stuff we need is on the first floor. Don't go any deeper, there are only b"
"ots in there."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:140
msgid "I wish you the best of luck."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:141
#: ./Spencer.dialog:149
#: ./Spencer.dialog:150
#: ./Spencer.dialog:160
#: ./Spencer.dialog:225
msgid "Opening a can of bots..."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:141
msgid ""
"I am supposed to clean out the first level of some warehouse. Sounds easy. It "
"lies nearby, somewhat hidden in the woods north-east of town."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:147
msgid "How is it going?"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:152
msgid ""
"Thanks to you, we've been able to transport all the goods we need right now. Y"
"ou've really helped us out there."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:153
msgid "Rest assured that we will never forget your brave activity for our community."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:155
msgid "Man, you really did it! I can hardly believe it, but all the bots are gone!"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:156
msgid ""
"Take these 500 circuits as a reward. And be assured that you've earned my deep"
"est respect, Linarian."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:157
msgid ""
"Our people are transporting the goods as we speak. It can't be too long until "
"new bots from ships in the orbit of the planet will beam down to replace the d"
"ead bots."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:160
msgid "Ouch. It wasn't. At least I am alive, and the warehouse is clear. *Whew*."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:163
msgid ""
"Not too good. Without the supplies from the warehouse we are doomed. So my pro"
"blems are still the same."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:164
msgid ""
"Maybe later, when you grow more experienced you might be able to help us after"
" all."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:167
msgid ""
"These are bad times. Interplanetary travel is made impossible by bot ships, so"
" we need to stick to our local resources."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:168
msgid ""
"We've got a list of stuff we need from the automated underground storage north"
" of town. But the bots there are numerous."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:169
msgid ""
"And currently I can't spare a single man from the town's defenses. It's quite "
"a difficult situation."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:175
msgid "Have I done enough quests to become a member now?"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:177
msgid "The yellow toolkit"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:178
msgid ""
"I think our teleporter service man, Dixon, has some problem. You might want to"
" talk to him."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:181
#: ./Spencer.dialog:188
#: ./Spencer.dialog:195
msgid "Dixon has his toolkit back."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:182
msgid ""
"He was in bad mood and told me he had to pay you for getting his own property "
"back."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:183
msgid "I think it is the best for him if we leave him alone the next days."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:184
msgid "I'm sure he has to do a lot now."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:189
msgid "He seemed quite aggressive and stressed."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:190
msgid ""
"Poor guy, if we weren't in such a bad situation, he could have some work-free "
"days, but bot attacks continue all the time."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:191
msgid "You better don't bother him the next days."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:196
msgid ""
"He did rail against you though. He said he had to give you 400 circuits to get"
" his toolkit back, his own property."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:197
msgid ""
"That was nearly all money he had. He said you were too greedy to become a good"
" member and he doesn't want to see you anymore."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:198
msgid ""
"I think everybody has to get a chance. But look ahead! When you are negatively"
" conspicuous again, we will ban you from our town!"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:201
msgid ""
"Dixon told me about the matter with his toolkit. He seemed pretty impressed by"
" you."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:207
msgid "Anything but the army snacks, please!"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:208
msgid ""
"When I was eating, Michelangelo told me about his renewed oven energy supply. "
"He seemed very pleased, and so was I."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:210
msgid ""
"I think you should visit the town's cook sometime. He's usually in the restaur"
"ant kitchen."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:213
msgid "Novice Arena"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:214
msgid "From Butch I hear you've become a novice arena master. Congratulations."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:216
msgid ""
"You might want to score some arena victories. That could also help your reputa"
"tion a lot."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:219
msgid "Bender's problem"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:220
msgid ""
"Helping Bender along was also a smart move. But you should be very careful wit"
"h that one. He can get mad rather easily. A bit of a security threat, but we c"
"an't be too picky."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:222
msgid "As far as I know, Bender is still very sick."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:226
msgid ""
"But most importantly, I was very impressed with you when you cleared out the w"
"arehouse. That was a huge deed I will never forget."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:228
msgid ""
"Personally I'm also worrying about how we will manage to get some necessary su"
"pplies from our warehouse. It's filled with bots and we just don't have the ma"
"npower to spare to clean them out."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:233
msgid ""
"OK. Your list of achievements is long enough. You can join us. So I hereby dec"
"lare you a member of the Red Guard."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:234
msgid ""
"But now that you are in the Guard, know this: There is only one rule for us gu"
"ards: We stick together. We survive together or we die together. But we do it "
"together."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:235
msgid ""
"And now you might want to inspect the guard house. Tell Tybalt to open the doo"
"r for you. Lukas at the arms counter will give you your armor."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:236
msgid "I hope you will prove yourself a worthy member of the Red Guard."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:237
msgid "Joined Town Guard!!"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:243
msgid ""
"All in all, not quite so bad. But you still need to do the one thing or the ot"
"her. Then we can talk about it."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:245
msgid ""
"I can't accept you into the guard like this. Get going. There are still many t"
"hings to do for you."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:251
msgid "I've heard Richard obtained new information on the town."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:253
msgid ""
"Yes, that's right, and in fact it might be crucial. As you may have heard, the"
" MS office is defended by a disruptor shield. They open it only to let out new"
" armies of bots."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:254
msgid ""
"The data on the cube he obtained indicates the existence of a secret experimen"
"tal facility in this region. Our findings suggest that they were testing some "
"new form of disruptor shield for MS, so the shield can be controlled from that"
" facility."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:255
msgid ""
"If the information is true, then you can take over the control droid and disab"
"le the shield permanently so we can get in."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:256
msgid ""
"We know that MS had a firmware update system, which could be used to propagate"
" a malicious update to disable all bots. It is very alluring, but to perform t"
"his trick you need to hack the control droid, which is in the heart of the HF."
" To enter HF you would have to disable the disruptor shield."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:257
msgid ""
"This seems like a gift sent from the heavens. Cleaning the Hell Fortress is no"
"t going to be easy, though.."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:262
msgid "I'd like to participate in this operation."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:264
msgid ""
"That's most kind of you to volunteer. So far, I've sent two scouts into the ar"
"ea. They have found the facility entrance and unlocked the gate."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:265
msgid ""
"That is a good sign, because it shows that the key combinations from the data "
"cube were correct."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:266
msgid ""
"However, we lost contact with them shortly after they went inside. They also r"
"eported heavy bot resistance."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:267
msgid ""
"I'd be glad if you could take a look. But use the utmost care. We can't afford"
" to lose another guard."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:272
msgid "OK. I'll be careful. But I'll do it."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:274
msgid ""
"Good. The base entrance is somewhat hidden in the caves to the northeast. Best"
" to use the north gate out of town, then head east, and turn north again along"
" the shore."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:275
msgid ""
"I wish you the best of luck for this operation. It might be that our survival "
"depends on it. Don't wait for assistance."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:276
msgid ""
"Try to get control over the disruptor shield if you can. The control droid sho"
"uld be somewhere on the lowest level of the installation. Simply destroying th"
"e droid might suffice in disabling the shield."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:277
msgid ""
"Spencer has revealed the information from the data cube evaluation to me. It s"
"eems there is an old military research facility north of the town. By taking o"
"ver the control droid, I should be able to control the disruptor shield at the"
" facility. I could activate it permanently, thereby locking off the Hell Fortr"
"ess, and the bots it's producing, forever. Alternatively, I could disable it, "
"and fight my way through the Hell Fortress droids until I reach the main contr"
"ol droid and update it, thereby disabling all bots in the entire area around t"
"own in one fell swoop."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:283
msgid "I don't feel like doing it now. I'd rather prepare some more."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:285
msgid "Good. You should be well prepared if you intend to go."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:286
msgid ""
"Also there is no need to hurry with this. After all, the installation is not r"
"unning away, so it's best to take a cautious approach."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:291
msgid ""
"It's done. Your soldiers were killed, but I managed to reach a computer termin"
"al that controls the shield. Access to the bot factory is now open, after I ch"
"anged the password on the terminal so as to prevent the bots from enabling the"
" shield again."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:293
msgid ""
"Good. We cannot help you much in this final mission, but I can tell you what o"
"ur recon teams gathered behind the factory doors. You will enter a zone that u"
"sed to be a MS office."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:294
msgid ""
"They carried out some development there, and had part of their patching divisi"
"on and update management department. The actual factory is located behind the "
"office."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:295
msgid ""
"With a bit of luck, you might not need to access it. We know they have their u"
"pdate server in the office."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:296
msgid ""
"If you can find it and get it to propagate a faulty update, this could suffice"
" to stopping bots dead in their tracks."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:297
msgid ""
"Look for the entrance of the office in the crystal fields. I will send a messa"
"ge to the guards so they let you pass. Then you will be on your own."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:298
msgid "Good luck."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:299
msgid ""
"I can now enter the fortress and find the upgrade server terminal. The fortres"
"s gates are in the Crystal Fields. Spencer told the guards to open the doors f"
"or me."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:304
msgid "I will need some time to get myself ready before I clean up the Hell Fortress."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:306
msgid "You had better be ready."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:310
msgid "I found someone out in the desert."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:312
msgid "Great, another mouth to feed."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:313
msgid "What is this person's name?"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:318
msgid "Tania"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:321
msgid "Well, since you are a guard member, I'll let you vouch for this Tania person."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:323
msgid "Well, we have enough food for now. I'll let this Tania person in."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:327
msgid ""
"I'd say you should take her straight away to Doc Moore, but he was found dead "
"earlier."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:328
msgid "You wouldn't happen to know anything about that, would you?"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:334
msgid ""
"You must take her straight away to Doc Moore. We can't have a disease breaking"
" out."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:336
#: ./Spencer.dialog:349
#: ./Spencer.dialog:351
#: ./Spencer.dialog:366
#: ./Spencer.dialog:370
#: ./Spencer.dialog:382
msgid "Tania's Escape"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:336
msgid ""
"Spencer said it was okay for Tania to enter the town, as long as she goes to s"
"ee Doc Moore first thing. Now all I have to do is tell her and Pendragon."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:342
msgid "No, of course not."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:344
msgid "Good."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:345
msgid "I didn't think it was you, but you never know."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:346
msgid ""
"About your friend, she can come in provided that she pulls her weight around h"
"ere."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:349
msgid ""
"When I asked about Tania entering the town, Spencer confronted me about Doc Mo"
"ore's death. I denyed everything and he bought it! He says it is OK for Tania "
"to enter the town: I should tell her and Pendragon."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:351
msgid ""
"When I asked about Tania entering the town, Spencer said Doc Moore was found d"
"ead! Oh, and Tania can enter the town. I should go tell her that."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:357
msgid "He and I had a disagreement, which we settled."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:359
msgid "I am the law here. If you have a problem, you come to me."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:361
msgid "I'm going to strip you of your membership in the Red Guard."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:364
msgid "Your friend can come in, but we will be watching the two of you closely."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:366
msgid ""
"When I asked about Tania entering the town, Spencer confronted me about Doc Mo"
"ore's death. I told him the truth, and he kicked me out of the Red Guard. But "
"he let Tania in, Now all I have to do is tell her and Pendragon."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:368
msgid "As the law, I pronounce you GUILTY of MURDER."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:369
msgid "The punishment is death."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:370
msgid ""
"When I asked about Tania entering the town, Spencer confronted me about Doc Mo"
"ore's death. He found me guilty of murder, and sentenced me to death."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:378
msgid "I killed him just to see what it was like. It was awesome."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:380
msgid "You are a sociopath, and a danger to us all!"
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:381
msgid "We must stop you before you kill again."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:382
msgid ""
"When I asked about Tania entering the town, Spencer confronted me about Doc Mo"
"ore's death. He found me too dangerous to live."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:389
msgid "I'll be going then."
msgstr ""

#: ./Spencer.dialog:391
msgid "See you later."
msgstr ""

